{"id":"creature","term":"Creature","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Denotes the whole creation in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 8:39\">Rom. 8:39</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Colossians 1:15\">Col. 1:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 5:13\">Rev. 5:13</a>; the whole human race in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 16:15\">Mark 16:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 8:19\">Rom. 8:19-22</a>.</p>\n<p>The living creatures in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 10:15\">Ezek. 10:15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 10:17\">17</a>, are imaginary beings, symbols of the Divine attributes and operations.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Romans 8:39","Colossians 1:15","Revelation 5:13","Mark 16:15","Romans 8:19","Ezekiel 10:15","Ezekiel 10:17"]}